    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix power control error in dlsch_alamouti function due to type mismatch\n\n### Summary\nThe `dlsch_alamouti` function was experiencing power control errors due to a type mismatch between the function signature and the actual data types being passed to it. The function was declared to take `int32_t **` parameters but was implemented with `int **` parameters, causing incorrect data interpretation and wrong power level calculations.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/LTE_UE_TRANSPORT/dlsch_demodulation.c`: Updated the `dlsch_alamouti` function signature to use `int32_t **` parameters instead of `int **` to match the function prototype, data structure definitions, and function calls.\n\n### Reproduction\nThe issue manifests as incorrect transmit power levels in UEs using Alamouti transmission mode. Users may observe:\n- UE transmit power levels that don't match expected values based on downlink measurements\n- Poor link performance or connection drops in environments where power control is critical\n- Inconsistent behavior between different hardware platforms due to varying memory alignment requirements\n\nTo reproduce:\n1. Configure a UE with Alamouti transmission mode (TM2)\n2. Monitor UE transmit power during operation\n3. Compare reported power levels with expected values based on downlink channel quality\n4. Observe discrepancies in power control behavior\n\nThe fix ensures that the function signature matches the data types used throughout the codebase, resolving the power control inaccuracies.\n"
}